Fortune telling and tarot reading in HK left me with nothing, but fears and worries. 
I doubt I mentioned that wendy and I went to Temple Street in HK for fortune and tarot reading, right? 
Perhaps I will just say a little on what those readings said. 

Fortune Telling 
I will get married between 28 to 30 years old. 

Tarot Reading ( It is a 6 months reading.) 
I will be with someone but it has a 3 to 4 months unknown period which there will be no contact. It is a triangle relationship which seems there, yet not there. Everything is full of uncertainy. It will end anyway, and I will get together with an unexpected person who is my friend. Future unknown. 

I do not want to get married, like duh! It is stupid and idiotic to get married, and get hurt after years. 
Triangle relationship? How can I get into this kind of thing? I dislikes being uncertained.  
The worst thing is to get together with a friend. What if it ended? Does that mean the friendship ended too? 
OMG! Can I just hide at home and not go through any of it? 

I definitely think that I am so gonna lose my hair, just to think of all these.

I am still unable to believe.
What seems to be not long ago was actually more than 15 years ago.
No longer the toddler I was.
I remember couple of weeks ago, we were looking at the old photo album.
Pictures taken with my mum seems so yesterday.
Yet I could see what time have left on my mum's face.
I was around 5 to 6 years old.
Not at some themepark with costly admission fees and exciting rides, not with some expensive toys I have.
Smiles on my face, indescribable satisfaction. Perhaps that is happiness to the ultimate simplicity.
I remember it was just three of us at MacRitchie Reservoir.
From the pictures we took, I was wearing a little skirt happily taking pictures with my mum.
I never understand till today.
The smile is an evidence of how secure I was feeling with my mum beside me.
From young, I always know that things would not be too bad as long as I have my mum with me.
Even when our house was hounded by loansharks because my father borrowed from them and disappeared.
She hugged the young shivering xiu xian.
She, a woman confronted the loansharks bravely, leaving them nothing to much to comment but a sentence.
"you are a brave woman daring enough to confront us, but you have got a coward as your husband."

Actually intended to talk about my feeling for the coming 21th I will be, but it just goes out of track.
Confusion in my mind, I do not wish to be 21 years old.
I know that the older I become, my mum would be older as well.
Dislike her saying that we will get the money once she die, and we will have the house as well.
Ultimately the day when I become 21 will still come, there is nothing I can do.

Because I am not feeling okay, I forced myself to exercise till I am dead tired. 
I am unhappy, I allow myself to indulge in unhealthy food for a little. 
I am autistic, I choose to eat alone. 

I actually do not understand my source of unhappiness. 
It just comes and goes like wind. 

It is not because of anything. 
It just come as a form of frustration, feeling irritated at everything. 

Being bored, I play game. 
Hopefully brighten up myself with the excitement from games. 
I played silly games like Ocean Express and The Gem Store. 
In love with these kind of games. 
I don't think anyone knows that I am a puzzle game lover, because I don't look that goofy.

During this very last minute of Year 2006, I am sitting comfortably in front of my computer with my pink dolphin, thinking of my resolutions for Year 2007.
I can hear popping sound, which is obviously firework in Malaysia.
I could have a chance of going to Vivocity and see a couple of friends there, but I gave it up anyway.
Going there alone makes me feel sad, just like I used to go Changi Village alone.
Believe me, I am happy. Year 2006 was not that saddening as it seems to be. Maybe for some people, but I happened to be out of it.
Year 2006 appeared to be a fruitful year to me, my thinking actually grow mature.

Firstly, I will like to apologise to people whom I have done wrong to.

How long can you like a person?
How long can friendship last?
How long can you live?

When a person says 'I will love you forever',
it is never true, for nothing lasts forever.
It only lasts throughout your life.

Don't measure by time,
it doesn't mean a shit.
It is the depth that matters.

The people who used to be there,
are still here.
The souls belong to them,
are just all gone.
Replaced by something different,
perhaps it is the coldness.

People do change, and it is really fast. 
Don't even think it will take months or years. 
It can simply be days, hours, minutes or even down to seconds. 
I chose not to say, but that doesn't mean I am not seeing it.

You should learn to be more observant.
Did anyone realise the fight between two big players in Singapore market is getting hot?

Firstly, it was the call charges.
One party is based on rate per minute while the other one is on this per second billing.
Then they always spend money creating cute or touching advertisements to influence consumers.

Secondly which is a more recent one, it is about "dedicated" or "shared" network.
Of course, they are insisting that their type of network is better in terms of internet traffic and beneficial for consumers.
Singnet's game (A rather stupid one actually) - Superwhiz
Information (starhub) - Shared VS Dedicated
Information (singnet) - Shared VS Dedicated

Last but not least (at least you should know it's a never-ending war), it is about the package that both of them are offering.
Starhub and Singnet are offering attractive items to attract the consumers to sign up or renew internet contracts with them.
Look at what they are offering, and you can see that they are merely trying to compete.
Starhub (Desktop) - Maxonline 6000 promo
Starhub (Notebook) - Maxonline 12000 /Ultimate promo
Singnet - Singnet Lenovo promo
